<h1>About Amalgam Magazine</h1><br/>
<p><strong>Amalgam:</strong> (a-mal-gam) <i>n.</i> - A combination of diverse elements; a mixture.<br/>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - <a href="http://dictionary.reference.com/search?q=amalgam">Dictionary.com</a></p>
<p>
Founded by Neil Gupta and Ruchi Srivastava in the December of 2005, Amalgam is "a magazine for the teens, by the teens," incorporating almost all the elements of a teenager's life. From popular debates and sciences to current music and fashions, this magazine helps to provide teens with not only general knowledge, but also helpful advice and amusing reads.</p>